(201, 1, 3, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Faith Salie and Dr. Heather Berlin, hosts of&nbsp;<em>Science Goes to the Movies</em>, discuss how common it is to hallucinate, as per author-neuorologist Oliver Sacks, particularly in creative individuals or artists.</p>\n\n<div>\n<div><iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="362" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/771qUreqSyA" width="640"></iframe></div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>', 'none', 'Scientists discuss how common it is to hallucinate like Michael Keaton''s character in "Birdman", especially with creative individuals and artists', 'none', 'Artists\nBirdman\nHallucinating\nMichael Keaton\nPsychology\nScience in Movies', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '[6] [birdman] Birdman', 'none', '[206] [minoff-debra] Debra Minoff', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(202, 1, 3, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>In <u>The Cosmic Connection</u>, the late astronomer Carl Sagan says that Clarke and Kubrick consulted with him on how to show extraterrestrial life. Kubrick apparently wanted some kind of humanoid representation, but Sagan argued that such alien life forms would not resemble our understanding of a physical life form. Rather than introduce "an element of falseness," Sagan advised Kubrick to suggest alien life rather than show it. Later, in a 1968 interview, Kubrick said that given millions of years of evolution, they decided that the alien life featured in the film evolved from physical entities to "immortal machine entities", and then into "beings of pure energy and spirit,&rdquo; with "limitless capabilities and ungraspable intelligence.&rdquo;</p>', 'none', 'Director Stanley Kubrick and writer Arthur C. Clarke consulted with astronomer Carl Sagan on how to show extraterrestrial life.', 'none', 'Science\nScience Fiction\nScience in Movies\nStanley Kubrick', 'xhtml', '2001.png', 'none', '[193] [2001-a-space-odyssey] 2001: A Space Odyssey', 'none', 'Screen Prism', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(203, 1, 3, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>In an interview with Joseph Gelmis in 1969, director Stanley Kubrick said that "[HAL] had an acute emotional crisis because he could not accept evidence of his own fallibility.&rdquo; This is suggested by HAL&rsquo;s assertion that no error has ever been made by a computer of his kind, even though the crew believes he has done just that.</p>\n\n<p>However, some believe HAL&rsquo;s breakdown was brought on by earlier problems. Both the film&rsquo;s sequel, 2010, and early drafts of the script suggest that authorities on Earth ordered HAL to withhold information from the astronauts regarding the true purpose of their mission. Some argue that doing so went created a conflict with HAL&rsquo;s basic programming, resulting in a gradual failure that led to his homicidal actions against the crew. To support this theory, some point out that HAL immediately misdiagnoses the hardware failure on the ship after he asks Bowman if he is disturbed by the &ldquo;mysteries&rdquo; and &ldquo;secrecy&rdquo; around the mission.</p>', 'none', '"He had an acute emotional crisis because he could not accept evidence of his own fallibility.”', 'none', 'Science\nScience Fiction\nStanley Kubrick', 'xhtml', '2001-A-Space-Odyssey-07.jpeg', 'none', '[193] [2001-a-space-odyssey] 2001: A Space Odyssey', 'none', 'Screen Prism', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(204, 1, 3, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Physicist Emily L. Rice explains how physicist Kip Thorne helped create visuals of black holes for the film&nbsp;<em>Interstellar</em>&nbsp;in this excerpted episode of&nbsp;<em>Science Goes to the Movies&nbsp;</em>presented by CUNY.tv.</p>\n\n<div><iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="362" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/IFUybbkzHS4" width="640"></iframe></div>', 'none', 'Physicist Emily L. Rice explains how physicist Kip Thorne helped create visuals of black holes for "Interstellar" to help audiences better understand the science behind black holes', 'none', 'Black holes\nChristopher Nolan\nInterstellar\nKip Thorne\nMatthew McConaughey\nphysics\nPhysics in Film\nScience in Film\nSpace', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '[116] [interstellar] Interstellar', 'none', '[206] [minoff-debra] Debra Minoff', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(205, 1, 1, 'Snowpiercer_poster.jpg', 'none', 'Bong Joon-ho', 'none', '1', 'none', 'Chris Evans\nSon Kang-ho\nTilda Swinton\nJamie Bell\nOctavia Spencer\nEwen Bremner\nGo Ah-sung\nJohn Hurt\nEd Harris', 'xhtml', '<p>Set in a future where a failed climate-change experiment kills all life on the planet except for a lucky few who boarded the Snowpiercer, a train that travels around the globe, where a class system emerges. &nbsp;Led by Curtis (Chris Evans), a ragtag group of lower-class citizens living in squalor at the back of the train, fight their way up to the front of the train (where the upper-class lives) in order to&nbsp;redistribute the wealth to all of the citizens on the train. &nbsp;With each section of the train they enter, they confront new obstacles that they must battle through in order to reach the front.</p>', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'Bong Joon-ho and Kelly Masterson ', 'none', '', NULL, 'Based on Comic Book\ncapitalism\ncaste system\nChris Evans\nclass differences\nClosed ecological system\nfather daughter relationship\nfather sone relationship\nIce\nJoon-ho Bong\nmother son relationship\nperpetual winter\npopulation control\npost apocalyptic world\nRebellion\nrevolt\nSnow\nSouth Korean Cinema\nTrain\ntunnel\nWinter', 'xhtml', 'Park Chan-wook, Lee Tae-hun, Jeong Tae-sung, Steven Nam', 'none', 'RADiUS-TWC (US), CJ Entertainment (South Korea)', 'none', '$40 million', 'none', '$86.8 million', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '95%', 'none', '84%', 'none', 'http://snowpiercer-film.com/', 'none', '<iframe width="854" height="510" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/nX5PwfEMBM0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
