(155, 1, 20, 3, NULL, 0, 5, 'Interview: Editor Sandra Adair', 'Film Comment', 'http://filmcomment.com/entry/interview-sandra-adair-boyhood', '"Those transitions were very purposefully designed by Rick. Not to take away from what I brought to the movie, but he and I had several conversations about that and we didn’t want to have a clear delineation between one year and the next year."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(156, 1, 145, 3, NULL, 0, 1, '"Breaking Bad"''s Bryan Cranston on the quiet desperation of Walt White', 'The Chicago Tribune', 'http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2008/02/breaking-bads-b.html\n', '"I’m thinking Walt developed a fear of success. At some point, for some reason, he failed to reach for that brass ring and got scared."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(157, 1, 145, 3, NULL, 0, 2, 'The dark art of "Breaking Bad"', 'The New York Times', 'http://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/10/magazine/the-dark-art-of-breaking-bad.html', '“I feel some sort of need for biblical atonement, or justice, or something,” Gilligan said. “I like to believe there is some comeuppance, that karma kicks in at some point, even if it takes years or decades to happen.”', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(158, 1, 145, 3, NULL, 0, 3, 'On "Breaking Bad," family is a motivation and a liability', 'The Atlantic', 'Reviews: http://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2012/07/on-breaking-bad-family-is-a-motivation-and-a-liability/260216/\n', 'Even the series'' most powerful characters have been brought down by their attachments to their loved ones.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(159, 1, 145, 3, NULL, 0, 4, 'Child''s play', 'The New Yorker', 'http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2012/08/27/childs-play-5', 'When the showrunner Vince Gilligan pitched “Breaking Bad” to AMC, he presented a mission statement, which amounted to a monumental spoiler: he would turn Mr. Chips into Scarface.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(160, 1, 20, 3, NULL, 0, 6, 'Richard Linklater and Ellar Coltrane: "Making ''Boyhood'' was a dear process"', 'Kate Kellaway, The Guardian', 'http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/jul/06/richard-linklater-ellar-coltrane-boyhood-interview-dear-process', '"Twelve years in the making, Richard Linklater''s Boyhood tells in real time the story of a boy called Mason – played, since he was six, by Ellar Coltrane. And seeing these two discuss the process is, well, like stepping into a conversation in a Linklater film…"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(161, 1, 148, 3, NULL, 0, 1, 'Screenwriter Beau Willimon talks "House Of Cards"', 'empireonline.com', 'http://www.empireonline.com/interviews/interview.asp?IID=1639', '"Where those two things intersect - one''s desire to serve and one''s desire to be selfish - is what makes our politicians seem like hypocrites."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(162, 1, 148, 3, NULL, 0, 2, 'The making of "House Of Cards" with David Fincher', 'empireonline.com', 'http://www.empireonline.com/interviews/interview.asp?IID=1636', '"The governing idea behind any bureaucracy is the funding of that bureaucracy, the perpetuation of that bureaucracy."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(163, 1, 148, 3, NULL, 0, 3, 'Political animals that slither: ‘House of Cards’ on Netflix stars Kevin Spacey', 'The New York Times', 'http://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/01/arts/television/house-of-cards-on-netflix-stars-kevin-spacey.html', 'Mr. Spacey is always compelling and perhaps to his credit he doesn’t ham it up the way he did in ‘Richard III’ or the way Mr. Richardson did in the BBC version. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(164, 1, 148, 3, NULL, 0, 4, '"House of Cards" is deliciously spiteful', 'The Los Angeles Times', 'http://articles.latimes.com/2013/feb/01/entertainment/la-et-st-house-of-cards-review-netflix-20130201', 'The show''s view of government may be off-puttingly jaundiced, but it''s impossible not to root for Frank. In this age of downsizing and infrastructure change, who hasn''t fantasized about devastating professional revenge?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(165, 1, 20, 3, NULL, 0, 7, 'Moment to Moment - Why Richard Linklater makes movies', 'Nathan Heller, The New Yorker', 'http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2014/06/30/moment-to-moment', '"Although few of Linklater’s films have much plot in the traditional sense, they lack the dead points and the aimlessness that many plotless movies have: they’re funny and buoyant, bouncing forward with an unself-conscious, joshing wit. Going against the fashions of contemporary filmmaking, Linklater’s notion of cinematic refinement has less to do with virtuosic camerawork than with creating a moment that’s worth capturing."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(166, 1, 155, 3, NULL, 0, 1, 'The murder mystery is beside the point in HBO’s existentialist cop drama "True Detective"', 'New York Magazine', 'http://www.vulture.com/2014/01/tv-review-hbos-true-detective.html', '"True Detective" is truly unsettling, not because it’s about the search for a Louisiana serial killer, but because soon enough the search seems almost incidental: a pretext for testing limits and acting out and debating what makes people tick.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(167, 1, 155, 3, NULL, 0, 2, 'If there’s a compelling reason to watch, Matthew McConaughey and Woody Harrelson provide it', 'The New York Times', 'http://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/11/arts/television/mcconaughey-and-harrelson-star-in-true-detective-on-hbo.html', 'The series reveals itself as a languid character study and a vehicle for long-winded exchanges about religion and responsibility that are writerly in the worst way.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(168, 1, 155, 3, NULL, 0, 3, 'Director Cary Fukunaga on "True Detective"', 'IndieWire', 'http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/interview-cary-fukunaga-on-hbo-series-true-detective-starring-matthew-mcconaughey-and-woody-harrelson-20130712', '"You have 8 hours of story sitting in your head, and moving pieces around so that when we get to here, will this be clear enough? Do I need to heighten this moment or stretch this one?"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(169, 1, 155, 3, NULL, 0, 4, 'Series writer Nic Pizzolatto on "True Detective"', 'The Wall Street Journal', 'http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2014/02/02/writer-nic-pizzolatto-on-thomas-ligotti-and-the-weird-secrets-of-true-detective/', '"I read Thomas Ligotti''s ''The Conspiracy Against the Human Race'' and found it incredibly powerful writing…I’d already been reading E.M. Cioran for years and consider him one of my all-time favorite and, oddly, most nourishing writers."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(170, 1, 155, 3, NULL, 0, 5, 'McConaughey reveals the four stages of "True Detective" Rustin Cohle', 'Rolling Stone', 'http://www.rollingstone.com/movies/news/mcconaughey-reveals-the-four-stages-of-true-detective-rustin-cohle-20140304', 'When Matthew McConaughey was preparing for the psychedelically complex character he plays in "True Detective," he made a monster document to help him find his way.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(171, 1, 155, 3, NULL, 0, 6, 'Her looming shadow grows: the complex women of "True Detective"', 'Molly Lambert, Grantland', 'http://grantland.com/hollywood-prospectus/her-looming-shadow-grows-the-women-of-true-detective/', '"A show that takes up misogyny as one of its main subjects isn’t necessarily misogynistic."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(172, 1, 155, 3, NULL, 0, 7, 'The shallow deep talk of “True Detective"', 'Emily Nussbaum, The New Yorker', 'http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2014/03/03/cool-story-bro', 'To state the obvious: while the male detectives of “True Detective” are avenging women and children, every live woman they meet is paper-thin.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(173, 1, 155, 3, NULL, 0, 8, '"True Detective": Who is the yellow king? Here are some theories.', 'vulture.com', 'http://www.vulture.com/2014/02/true-detective-who-is-the-yellow-king.html', 'The knowledge that the Yellow King is a name taken from stories about vaguely supernatural stuff has inspired some grand theoretical leaps.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(174, 1, 145, 3, NULL, 0, 5, 'Vince Gilligan walks us through season four of "Breaking Bad"', 'The A.V. Club', 'http://www.avclub.com/article/vince-gilligan-walks-us-through-season-four-of-ibr-63013', '"Season two was the only season where we knew exactly where we would end at the beginning of it all."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(175, 1, 145, 3, NULL, 0, 6, 'Vince Gilligan shares 5 alternate endings to "Breaking Bad"', 'The Wrap', 'http://www.thewrap.com/breaking-bad-vince-gilligan-shares-5-alternate-endings/', 'No. 1: Walter White goes Rambo...', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(176, 1, 62, 3, NULL, 0, 5, 'The great American shooter', 'J. Hoberman, The New York Review of Books', 'http://www.nybooks.com/blogs/nyrblog/2015/feb/13/great-american-shooter/', 'For all its patriotic rhetoric, "American Sniper" is not a moral lesson but a tragedy. The causal link Eastwood establishes between the trauma of September 11 and the catastrophe of Iraq is less the dramatization of history than an illustration of historical paralysis—elaborating the implications of an endless, unwinnable war. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(177, 1, 20, 3, NULL, 0, 8, 'It''s about time', 'Holly Willis, Film Comment', 'http://www.filmcomment.com/article/richard-linklater-boyhood', 'Linklater’s latest temporal gambit shouldn’t come as too much of a surprise. Anyone familiar with the director’s increasingly sophisticated body of work knows that time is a recurring theme.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(178, 1, 6, 3, NULL, 0, 5, 'Easy virtue', 'Angelo Muredda, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/currency/easy-virtue-alejandro-gonzalez-inarritus-birdman/', 'For all its carping about the virtues of unfettered creativity, "Birdman" is little more than a rote confirmation of what middlebrow artists and prestige-charmed critics already believe: that a little formal bombast, shallowly conceived and laboriously, ostentatiously achieved, is all one needs to make great art.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(179, 1, 114, 3, NULL, 0, 5, 'Pursuits of happiness', 'Adam Nayman, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/currency/pursuits-happiness-david-finchers-gone-girl/', '"Gone Girl"’s portrait of domestic bliss as a kind of personalized thermonuclear détente is glib and obvious, but it’s also deeply satisfying.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(180, 1, 111, 3, NULL, 0, 5, 'Last rites', 'Adam Nayman, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/currency/last-rites-bennett-millers-foxcatcher/', '"Foxcatcher" is a funereal film, tastefully arrayed by a team of gifted morticians. Whether one finds it more morbid than mournful is another matter.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(181, 1, 112, 3, NULL, 0, 7, 'Cannes 2014 | "Adieu au langage"', 'Blake Williams, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/spotlight/adieu-au-langage-jean-luc-godard-france/', '"Adieu au language" is a lashing out against the symbolic and semiotic structures that hinder our ability to experience truth in the world, and laments the freedoms lost from so many demarcations and hierarchies, while painfully acknowledging the impossibility of the world without them.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(182, 1, 20, 3, NULL, 0, 9, 'What is "Boyhood"?', 'Gabe Klinger, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/features/boyhood/', 'Here are 12 aspects of "Boyhood" - one for each year that the film covers - that attempt to explain what Linklater and his collaborators might be up to.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(183, 1, 70, 3, NULL, 0, 9, 'TIFF 2014 | "Whiplash"', 'Angelo Muredda, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/cinema-scope-online/tiff-2014-whiplash-damien-chazelle-us-special-presentations/', 'If one gets the sense that Chazelle hasn’t quite worked out whether Fletcher is an unorthodox teacher or just a bully, it’s ultimately to his film’s credit; if nothing else, that ambivalence puts it up there with "At Berkeley" on the shortlist of feel-bad movies about higher education.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(184, 1, 113, 3, NULL, 0, 7, 'cinema scope: "Under the Skin"', 'Blake Williams, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/currency/skin-jonathan-glazer-uk/', 'In the opening minutes of his decade-in-the-making science-fiction film "Under the Skin," Jonathan Glazer positions himself as the latest heir to Stanley Kubrick the Millennials have been clamouring for.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(185, 1, 105, 3, NULL, 0, 7, 'cinema scope: "Inherent Vice"', 'Blake Williams, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/currency/inherent-vice-paul-thomas-anderson-us/', 'We can’t expect a literary adaptation to provide the same kind of syntactic energy that we’d find in Pynchon''s source text. The challenge is to compensate for the loss of such a vital aesthetic design with another of the same calibre. This is where Anderson slips.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(186, 1, 30, 3, NULL, 0, 7, 'cinema scope: "The Grand Budapest Hotel"', 'Julian Carrington, cinema scope', 'http://cinema-scope.com/currency/grand-budapest-hotel-wes-anderson-usgermany/', '"The Grand Budapest Hotel" further affirms its writer-director’s revitalization even as it rearticulates his fixations with mourning and ruptured relationships, as well as his palpable fascination with bygone eras. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
