(30, 1, 30, 'Wes Anderson''s THE GRAND BUDAPEST HOTEL', 'Wes Anderson, The Grand Budapest Hotel, Ralph Fiennes, Edward Norton, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Awards, aspect, ratio', 'Wes Anderson''s THE GRAND BUDAPEST HOTEL'),
(6, 1, 6, 'Screen Prism - Alejandro González Iñárritu''s BIRDMAN', 'Birdman, Alejandro, González, Iñárritu, Michael, Keaton, Batman, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Awards, Emmanuel, Lubezki, comic, book', 'Alejandro González Iñárritu''s BIRDMAN at ScreenPrism - where all of your film and TV related questions are answered'),
(26, 1, 26, 'What is so groundbreaking about "Boyhood"?', 'Richard, Linklater, Boyhood, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Austin, Texas, Indie, Spirit, Awards', 'Richard Linklater filmed "Boyhood" across 12 years, following a young boy''s journey from childhood, to adolescence and eventually into young adulthood. Such an ambitious film process is nearly unprecedented in the history of cinema.'),
(31, 1, 31, 'How did "The Grand Budapest Hotel" draw on history?', 'Wes, Anderson, Ralph, Fiennes, Grand, Budapest, Hotel, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Awards, aspect, ratio, war, history, WWI, WWII, World, Nazis, Third, Reich, Germany, Vienna, Austria, Cold War', 'Different eras of "The Grand Budapest Hotel" seem to reflect the respective geopolitical realities of those eras in actual history, whether it’s the Cold War of the 1960s or a 1930s setting colored by both world wars flanking either side of the decade.'),
(27, 1, 27, 'Has Richard Linklater ever made anything that anticipated "Boyhood"''s innovations?', 'Richard, Linklater, Boyhood, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Austin, Texas, Indie, Spirit, Awards, Before, Sunrise, Sunset, Midnight', 'Richard Linklater’s films have been notable for exploring the passage of time. "Boyhood" is arguably his most ambitious and focused work in this mode, and in many ways, it feels like the apotheosis of his body of work.'),
(32, 1, 32, 'Who is Stefan Zweig? Why does he receive the first credit at the end of Wes Anderson''s "The Grand Budapest Hotel"?', 'Stefan, Zweig, Wes, Anderson, Grand, Budapest, Hotel, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Awards', 'Austrian author Stefan Zweig was an exile, like Zero Moustafa. Of his writings, the film seems particularly reminiscent of “The World of Yesterday,” which was written when Zweig was fleeing from the new Nazi regime.'),
(161, 1, 161, '', '', ''),
(160, 1, 160, '', '', ''),
(19, 1, 19, '', '', ''),
(20, 1, 20, 'ScreenPrism - Richard Linklater''s BOYHOOD', 'Richard Linklater, Boyhood, IFC, Ethan Hawke, Patricia Arquette, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Austin, Texas, Indie, Spirit, Awards', 'Richard Linklater''s BOYHOOD at ScreenPrism - where all of your film and TV related questions are answered'),
(21, 1, 21, 'What does "Birdman" have to do with Michael Keaton’s past role as Batman?', 'Birdman, Alejandro, González, Iñárritu, Michael, Keaton, Batman, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Emmanuel, Lubezki, comic, book', 'The role wasn''t written with Michael Keaton in mind, but his past career definitely helped the film.'),
(22, 1, 22, 'Is it true that the film was made to look like one continuous take without any cuts?', 'Birdman, Alejandro, González, Iñárritu, Michael, Keaton, Batman, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Emmanuel, Lubezki, comic, book, Children, Men', 'They took some tricks from "Children of Men" and stretched them even further.'),
(23, 1, 23, 'What''s the big deal about "Birdman"? Was it necessary to be filmed to look like one continuous take?', 'Birdman, Alejandro, González, Iñárritu, Michael, Keaton, Batman, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Awards, Emmanuel, Lubezki', '"Birdman" is shot to look like one long continuous take without camera cuts.  Unbroken takes often bring a film closer to live theater and, in this case, parallel the story.'),
(24, 1, 24, 'Does Riggan Thomson (Michael Keaton) actually have super powers?', 'Birdman, Alejandro, González, Iñárritu, Michael, Keaton, Batman, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Emmanuel, Lubezki, comic, book', 'The film does seem to indulge in a bit of whimsical “magical realism.”'),
(25, 1, 25, 'What''s "Birdman" really about? Is it critiquing the dominance of comic book films in Hollywood?', 'Birdman, Alejandro, González, Iñárritu, Michael, Keaton, Batman, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Emmanuel, Lubezki, comic, book', 'Riggan Thomson’s reasons for putting on this production are constantly defined by how he wants to be appreciated by the public.'),
(28, 1, 28, 'How did Richard Linklater work with the passing of time in "Boyhood"', 'Richard, Linklater, Boyhood, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Austin, Texas, Indie, Spirit, Awards', 'Albeit fictional, "Boyhood" aspires towards documentary form by consciously opening up to reality, particularly by showing the real life effect of time on the actors, whether through aging or the experiences in their own personal lives.'),
(29, 1, 29, 'Did the rapid technological changes within the industry impact the way "Boyhood" was made?', 'Richard, Linklater, Boyhood, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Austin, Texas, Indie, Spirit, Awards, 35mm film', 'Richard Linklater insisted that they shoot the movie on 35mm film until the very end.'),
(33, 1, 33, 'What’s so unique about the art direction in "The Grand Budapest Hotel"?', 'Wes, Anderson, Ralph, Fiennes, Grand, Budapest, Hotel, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Awards, aspect, ratio', 'Wes Anderson: “The particular brand of artificiality that I like to use is an old-fashioned one.”'),
(34, 1, 34, 'What''s the significance behind the three different aspect ratios in "The Grand Budapest Hotel"?', 'Wes, Anderson, Ralph, Fiennes, Grand, Budapest, Hotel, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Awards, aspect, ratio', 'Wes Anderson filmed "The Grand Budapest Hotel" in three different aspect ratios to reflect the history of cinema during those periods (1930s, 1960s and 1980s).'),
(35, 1, 35, 'Where did they come up with the painting at the heart of "The Grand Budapest Hotel"?', 'Wes, Anderson, Ralph, Fiennes, Grand, Budapest, Hotel, independent, film, Oscars, Academy, Awards, Golden, Globes, Indie, Spirit, Awards, aspect, ratio, boy, with, apple, painting', '"Boy with Apple" really is priceless, as an art history in-joke.'),
