(38, 1, 38, 'Why is Alan Turing considered the “father” of computers, and how did he help win World War II?', 'Imitation, Game, Morten, Tyldum, Alan, Turing, Benedict, Cumberbatch, Keira, Knightley, Graham, Moore, homosexuality, Bletchley, Park, war, World, War, II, WWII, Enigma, Nazi, Nazis, Third, Reich, homosexual, gay, rights, computers, artificial, intelligence', 'Turing created a machine that was able to crack Nazi Germany’s Enigma Code.'),
(39, 1, 39, 'How did Alan Turing become an important figure for gay rights?', 'Imitation, Game, Morten, Tyldum, Alan, Turing, Benedict, Cumberbatch, Keira, Knightley, Graham, Moore, homosexuality, Bletchley, Park, war, World, War, II, WWII, Enigma, Nazi, Nazis, Third, Reich, homosexual, gay, rights, computers, artificial, intelligence', 'Until the late 1960s, homosexuality was treated as criminal behavior in the UK.'),
(40, 1, 40, 'Why has "The Imitation Game"''s depiction of Alan Turing’s homosexuality been criticized?', 'Imitation, Game, Morten, Tyldum, Alan, Turing, Benedict, Cumberbatch, Keira, Knightley, Graham, Moore, homosexuality, Bletchley, Park, war, World, War, II, WWII, Enigma, Nazi, Nazis, Third, Reich, homosexual, gay, rights, computers, artificial, intelligence', '"The Imitation Game" has been criticized for avoiding any sort of physical intimacy between Turing and another man.'),
(41, 1, 41, 'Is "The Imitation Game" more fiction than fact?', 'Imitation, Game, Morten, Tyldum, Alan, Turing, Benedict, Cumberbatch, Keira, Knightley, Graham, Moore, homosexuality, Bletchley, Park, war, World, War, II, WWII, Enigma, Nazi, Nazis, Third, Reich, homosexual, gay, rights, computers, artificial, intelligence', 'A substantial portion of the film is actually fiction.'),
(42, 1, 42, 'What is the significance of the film''s title? What is "the imitation game"?', 'Imitation, Game, Morten, Tyldum, Alan, Turing, Benedict, Cumberbatch, Keira, Knightley, Graham, Moore, homosexuality, Bletchley, Park, war, World, War, II, WWII, Enigma, Nazi, Nazis, Third, Reich, homosexual, gay, rights, computers, artificial, intelligence', 'The film''s title relates to some of Turing’s most important work, but it’s at best peripheral to the film’s plot.'),
