(6887, 9, 1, 1426058062, '54334133a1b9b798a1f7b5b29e7e7f4f', NULL, '<section class="main">\n  <div class="content single thoughts feature">\n  <article class="q-and-a">\n      <header>\n        <h1>Is hallucinating common for creative artists like in &#8220;Birdman&#8221;</h1>\n        \n        <h5>Related: <a href="http://screenprism.dev/film/page/birdman">Birdman</a></h5>\n        \n        <p class="by-line"> <span class="spacer">|</span> <time datetime="2015-03-04T1303">March 4, 2015</time> <span class="spacer">|</span> <a href="#discussion"><svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" class="icon comment-icon"><use xlink:href="#comment-icon"></use></svg> <span class="disqus-comment-count" data-disqus-url="http://screenprism.dev/insights/article/is-hallucinating-common-for-creative-artists-like-in-birdman">0</span></a></p>\n      </header>\n      <div class="article-body">\n        <p>Faith Salie and Dr. Heather Berlin, hosts of&nbsp;<em>Science Goes to the Movies</em>, discuss how common it is to hallucinate, as per author-neuorologist Oliver Sacks, particularly in creative individuals or artists.</p>\n\n<div>\n<div><iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="362" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/771qUreqSyA" width="640"></iframe></div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n      </div>\n      <footer>\n        <ul class="tags">\n        \n          <li><a href="http://screenprism.dev/insights/tag/Artists">Artists</a></li>\n        \n          <li><a href="http://screenprism.dev/insights/tag/Birdman">Birdman</a></li>\n        \n          <li><a href="http://screenprism.dev/insights/tag/Hallucinating">Hallucinating</a></li>\n        \n          <li><a href="http://screenprism.dev/insights/tag/Michael-Keaton">Michael Keaton</a></li>\n        \n          <li><a href="http://screenprism.dev/insights/tag/Psychology">Psychology</a></li>\n        \n          <li><a href="http://screenprism.dev/insights/tag/Science-in-Movies">Science In Movies</a></li>\n        \n        </ul>\n      </foot